Paper: hep-th/9602106

Date: 1996-02-20

Title: Comment on ``New pseudoclassical model for Weyl particles"

Authors: Jose L. Cortes and Mikhail S. Plyushchay

Comments: 4 pages, LaTeX, submitted to Phys. Rev. D

It is demonstrated that the recently proposed pseudoclassical model for Weylparticles [1] (D.M. Gitman, A.E. Goncalves and I.V. Tyutin, Phys. Rev. D 50(1994) 5439) is classically inconsistent. A possible way of removing theclassical inconsistency of the model is proposed.